OL,3,CSoldier F defence costs government
OL,4,C#4.3m
OL,6,FThe UK Government has spent
OL,7,F#4.3million so far on the defence of a
OL,8,Fformer paratrooper accused of two
OL,9,Fmurders during the events of Bloody
OL,10,FSunday.
OL,12,FThe veteran, known as Soldier F for
OL,13,Flegal reasons, was found not guilty of
OL,14,Ftwo murders and five attempted murders
OL,15,Fin Londonderry in 1972 following a
OL,16,Fjudge-led trial at Belfast Crown Court.
OL,18,FThirteen people were killed when
OL,19,Fmembers of the Parachute Regiment
OL,20,Fopened fire on crowds following a
OL,21,Fcivil rights demonstration in the city.
